question: Find all films rented by customer "John Doe."

  ON f.film_id = i.film_id

  ON r.customer_id = c.customer_id

generator_responses:

FROM film AS f
WHERE f.film_id NOT IN (
    SELECT i.film_id
    FROM inventory AS i
)
AND EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM rental AS r
    WHERE r.inventory_id IN (
        SELECT i.inventory_id
        FROM inventory AS i
        WHERE i.film_id = f.film_id
    )
    AND r.rental_date >= (NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days')
);", 'explanation': "The query first selects the distinct titles from the film table. It then filters these films based on two conditions. The first condition ensures that the film's film_id is not present in the inventory table. The second condition uses an EXISTS clause to check if there exists a rental record for the film's inventory_id within the last 30 days. This ensures that only films that are not in the inventory and have been rented within the last 30 days are returned."}

SELECT DISTINCT f.title
FROM film AS f
WHERE f.film_id NOT IN (
    SELECT i.film_id
    FROM inventory AS i

FROM film f

JOIN payment p ON r.rental_id = p.rental_id
GROUP BY f.title
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC
LIMIT 5;
